/// Manifold-Constrained Hyper-Connection (mHC)
///
/// Extends Hyper-Connections with manifold constraints for training stability.
/// Projects the residual mixing matrix H_res onto the Birkhoff polytope
/// (set of doubly stochastic matrices) via Sinkhorn-Knopp normalization.
///
/// Key properties of the doubly stochastic constraint:
/// 1. Norm preservation: spectral norm <= 1 (non-expansive, prevents explosion)
/// 2. Compositional closure: product of doubly stochastic matrices is doubly stochastic
/// 3. Signal conservation: preserves global mean across layers
/// 4. Geometric interpretation: convex combination of permutations (Birkhoff polytope)
///
/// The H_pre and H_post mappings are additionally constrained to be non-negative
/// (via sigmoid) to prevent signal cancellation.
///
/// Parameters:
/// - layer: The sublayer (attention or FFN) to wrap
/// - n: Expansion factor for residual stream width (typically 4)
/// - dim: Model dimension
/// - layer_idx: Layer index for per-layer parameters
/// - alpha_init: Gating factor initialization (default: 0.01, per paper)
/// - sinkhorn_iters: Number of Sinkhorn-Knopp iterations (default: 20)
///
/// Shape Contract:
/// - Input: [*batch, n, dim] — expanded residual stream (n parallel streams)
/// - Output: [*batch, n, dim] — updated residual stream after layer + mixing
///
/// For n=1, degenerates to standard residual connection (identity mapping).
///
/// Reference: Xie et al. (2026) "mHC: Manifold-Constrained Hyper-Connections"
/// arXiv:2512.24880v2 (DeepSeek-AI)
neuron ManifoldHyperConnect(layer: Neuron, n, dim, layer_idx, alpha_init=0.01, sinkhorn_iters=20):
    in: [*batch, n, dim]
    out: [*batch, n, dim]
    impl: neuroscript,connections/ManifoldHyperConnect
